readObject

private void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
Read OAObject data. Note: This method must stay "private" or it will never be called. It does not need to be subclassed because any object that is a subclass should have its own readObject() method. ObjectInputStream.readObject() calls the readObject() for each class, superClass, and subClass individually.
